  "text": "It has been widely assumed that the scope of quantifiers is determined by the c-command relationship between quantifiers at LF (May 1977, Aoun & [CITATION_1] others) . If a and b are quantifiers and a c-commands b at LF, a takes scope over b. Let us first consider the following raising construction from Fox (1999) : (35) One soldier is expected (by Napoleon) [ TP tk to t die in every battle].",
